<https://w3id.org/iiot-pmo> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<https://w3id.org/iiot-pmo> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <https://w3id.org/iiot-pmo/0.2.0> .
<https://w3id.org/iiot-pmo> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Version 0.2.0 extends the initial predictive maintenance ontology with LLM-assisted ontology population, maintenance history, time-series batches, and machine-learning-based predicted failures."@en .
<https://w3id.org/iiot-pmo> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/references> <https://doi.org/10.1002/cpe.7420> .
<https://w3id.org/iiot-pmo> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/references> <https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-47240-4_22> .
<https://w3id.org/iiot-pmo> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/references> <https://doi.org/10.1016/j.knosys.2024.112940> .
<https://w3id.org/iiot-pmo> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Industrial IoT & Predictive Maintenance Ontology (IIoT-PMO)"@en .
<https://w3id.org/iiot-pmo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Developed according to a METHONTOLOGY-inspired lifecycle: specification, conceptualization, formalization, implementation, and evaluation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/iiot-pmo> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo> "0.2.0" .
